        Add a conditional Distribution to the current scratch property
        Specified by:
        scratch_addConditionalDistribution in interface UI_Interface
        Parameters:
        dependencyConditions - A map of integer IDs, which must be one of the IDs from UI_Interface.scratch_getDependencies()(); and a label that the dependency must be, which is one of the labels in the node property. All pIDs are optional, but there must be exactly one label per pID.
        probabilities - A map of all the range labels in the scratch property to floating point values representing the probability of that range in the distribution.       • scratch_commitToNodeProperties

        public int scratch_commitToNodeProperties()
                                   throws UI_Interface.UIException
        Description copied from interface: UI_Interface
        Finalize the scratch property and add it to the structure of node properties. In its current state, this clears the scratch property automatically, and there is no way to edit or remove an added node property, so it is important to make sure the property is how the user wants it before committing.
        Specified by:
        scratch_commitToNodeProperties in interface UI_Interface
        Returns:
        The node property ID of the new property, which is also available through UI_Interface.nodeProp_getPropertyIDs()
        Throws:
        UI_Interface.UIException - There are several reasons that this exception may be thrown, here is a list of examples:
        • The scratch property is null, which means UI_Interface.scratch_new(String, String, String) was never called
        • The scratch property has the same name as another node property
        • The scratch property does not have a default distribution, but needs one.
        And various other messages. Throwable.getMessage() should yield more information.
